.TH nanolx-skel 1 "2026 May 19"
.SH NAME
nanolx-ctx
.SH SYNOPSIS
nanolx-skel [enable] [disable]
.SH DESCRIPTION          \" Section Header - required - don't modify
nanolx-skels modifies \fI/etc/default/useradd\fP to set the default shell for
newly created users to \fI/usr/bin/bash\fP and changes the skeleton config files
to use from \fI/etc/skel\fP to \fI/usr/share/nanolx/skel\fP

.SH OPTIONS
nanolx-skel knows the following options
.PP
.TP 4
.B enable
Set default shell to bash and enable nanolx skeleton for new users.
.TP
.B disable
Revert to system defaults.
.TP
.PP

